The defendant Emilio O Cornejo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing [Modifiers: Penalty - Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Emilio O Cornejo in court with attorney Vincent Paul Guimont.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.

Report received.  Defendant is testing negative and has attended all appointment.  Defendant needs to begin community service.  Review hearing scheduled for January 12, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Emilio O Cornejo in court with attorney Vincent Paul Guimont.  Lucy Kronforst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement.
The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the case transferred to Judge Brostrom, Branch 6 for a Review Hearing.  Review hearing scheduled for October 6, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
